[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wildflower meadow created at Toyota car plant in Derbyshire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The Toyota car factory in Derbyshire has joined forces with Kew Gardens to create wild flower meadows on its land.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
9 June 2014 Last updated at 16:25 BST
Tony Walker, deputy managing director of the company, said the firm was leading the way in what could be done to help the environment.
He added that it would also save the business money.
Simon Hare reports for East Midlands Today.
